definition: to cover/to wrap/to hold/to include/to take charge of/to contract (to or for)/package/wrapper/container/bag/to hold or embrace/bundle/packet/CL:個|个[ge4],隻|只[zhi1]

sentences.chinese: 这件邮包盖着伦敦的邮戳。

sentences.english: The package was neatly wrapped and carried extra insurance.
sentences.chinese: 邮包包得很整齐，并加了额外保险。

sentences.english: The pracel you post must be well packed.
sentences.chinese: 你所寄的邮包必须妥善包装。

sentences.english: I will have the parcel expressed to your office by a courier.
sentences.chinese: 我会请速递员将邮包快捷传递到你的办公室。

sentences.english: Enclose this form, the warranty card, and the purchase receipt in your package.
sentences.chinese: 请在您的邮包中放入此表，保修卡及购货发票。

sentences.english: Philip tore at  the wrapping of the postal parcel.
sentences.chinese: 菲利普用力撕邮包的包装纸。

sentences.english: In this paper a real time Parcel Post Checking Speech Recognition System is developed.
sentences.chinese: 本文研究开发了一套邮包信息校核语音识别系统。

sentences.english: We can't accept registered packages sealed with Scotch tape.
sentences.chinese: 我们不收用这种东西封的挂号邮包。

sentences.english: Every day he rides on a bike with a mailbag from one house to another.
sentences.chinese: 每天他骑着自行车，带着邮包从一家转到另一家。

sentences.english: He gave the mail to me, then high-tailed.
sentences.chinese: 他把邮包交给我后就匆忙走了。

sentences.english: All the postal parcels had been lashed up before they were dispatched.
sentences.chinese: 所有邮包在发出之前都已捆牢了。

definition: to sign for the acceptance of sth (e.g. a delivery etc)
